title: PBS: Bill Moyers Journal, Friday, November 7, 2008

KEVIN PHILLIPS 

Does Barack Obama&#039;s victory mean a new and permanent political alignment in American politics? Bill Moyers speaks with Kevin Phillips about how America has changed since Phillips penned THE EMERGING REPUBLICAN MAJORITY 40 years ago. 



AMERICAN HISTORY LESSONS 

Bill Moyers sits down with Columbia University professor Eric Foner, who specializes in political and African-American history, and Patricia J. Williams, a professor of law at Columbia University. 



 



VIEWERS ON WHAT&#039;S NEXT?

JOURNAL viewers lay out their priorities for the next administration. 



MOYERS ON TERKEL AND LEONARD

A Bill Moyers essay on the loss of Studs Terkel and John Leonard.
